                  <tr><th>Type</th><th>Standard</th><th>High Physical Support</th></tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr><td>Weekday</td><td>$346.51</td><td>$412.15</td></tr>
                  <tr><td>Saturday</td><td>$384.92</td><td>$457.68</td></tr>
                  <tr><td>Sunday</td><td>$423.32</td><td>$503.20</td></tr>
                  <tr><td>Public Holiday</td><td>$461.72</td><td>$548.72</td></tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
              <p class="mt-2">These are maximum NDIS price limits - providers may charge less.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="collapse collapse-plus bg-white border border-base-200 rounded-2xl">
            <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
            <div class="collapse-title text-lg font-bold text-secondary">
              How much does respite care cost per week NDIS?
            </div>
            <div class="collapse-content text-secondary/70">
              <p>NDIS respite care for a typical 7-night week costs:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1">
                <li><strong>5 weekdays + 2 weekend days</strong>: ~$2,540</li>
                <li><strong>All weekdays (Mon-Sun start)</strong>: ~$2,426</li>
                <li><strong>Including a public holiday</strong>: Add ~$115</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-2">High Physical Support STA adds approximately 20% to these costs. Two weeks of respite typically costs $5,000-$5,500 for standard support.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="collapse collapse-plus bg-white border border-base-200 rounded-2xl">
            <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
            <div class="collapse-title text-lg font-bold text-secondary">
              What is the difference between NDIS respite care and STA?
            </div>
            <div class="collapse-content text-secondary/70">
              <p><strong>Respite care and STA are the same thing</strong> - just different names for the same NDIS support:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1">
                <li><strong>STA (Short Term Accommodation)</strong> is the official NDIS term</li>
                <li><strong>Respite care</strong> is the common/traditional name</li>
                <li>Both refer to temporary overnight accommodation with support</li>
                <li>Funded under Core Supports in your NDIS plan</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-2">STA provides a break for carers (respite) while also giving participants opportunities to try new things, build independence, or recover after hospital stays.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="collapse collapse-plus bg-white border border-base-200 rounded-2xl">
            <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
            <div class="collapse-title text-lg font-bold text-secondary">
              What NDIS line item codes are used for respite/STA?
            </div>
            <div class="collapse-content text-secondary/70">
              <p>The main NDIS line item codes for STA (respite) are:</p>
              <table class="table table-sm mt-2">
                <thead>
                  <tr><th>Code</th><th>Description</th><th>Rate</th></tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr><td class="font-mono">01_799_0104_1_1</td><td>STA - Weekday</td><td>$346.51</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="font-mono">01_799_0104_1_1_S</td><td>STA - Saturday</td><td>$384.92</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="font-mono">01_799_0104_1_1_U</td><td>STA - Sunday</td><td>$423.32</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="font-mono">01_799_0104_1_1_P</td><td>STA - Public Holiday</td><td>$461.72</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="font-mono">01_800_0104_1_1</td><td>STA High Physical - Weekday</td><td>$412.15</td></tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
              <p class="mt-2">Use our <a href="/tools/ndis-code-lookup" class="text-primary hover:underline">NDIS Code Lookup tool</a> to find all STA-related codes.</p>
            </div>
